import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="darkgrid")
    sns.countplot(x="Effect_Amount_of_damage", data=data, palette="Set2")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of Effect_Amount_of_damage?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Effect Amount of Damage")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.countplot(x="Wildlife_Species", data=data, order=data['Wildlife_Species'].value_counts().iloc[:10].index, palette="Set2")
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    chart.axhline(y=data['Wildlife_Species'].value_counts().iloc[0], color='r', linestyle='--', label='Most common species: {:.2f}'.format(data['Wildlife_Species'].value_counts().iloc[0]))
    chart.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x=data['Speed_IAS_in_knots'], ax=ax, color='blue')
    ax.axvline(data['Speed_IAS_in_knots'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['Speed_IAS_in_knots'].median()))
    ax.axvline(data['Speed_IAS_in_knots'].quantile(0.25), color='green', linestyle='--', label='Q1: {:.2f}'.format(data['Speed_IAS_in_knots'].quantile(0.25)))
    ax.axvline(data['Speed_IAS_in_knots'].quantile(0.75), color='orange', linestyle='--', label='Q3: {:.2f}'.format(data['Speed_IAS_in_knots'].quantile(0.75)))
    ax.set_xlabel('Speed (IAS in knots)')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of Speed_IAS_in_knots?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax = sns.countplot(x='Wildlife_Size', data=data, palette='Set2')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of Wildlife_Size?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Wildlife Size')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    for p in ax.patches:
        ax.annotate(f'{p.get_height()}', (p.get_x()+0.3, p.get_height()+10))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
